//! `str.casefold`). Each entry is a codepoint whose fold differs from its simple
//! lowercase mapping — the multi-character "full" folds (e.g. `ß` -> `ss`) plus
//! the handful of single-char folds that lowercasing gets wrong. Every other
//! codepoint folds identically to `char::to_lowercase`, so `str.casefold` uses
//! this table only as an override and defers to lowercasing otherwise. Sorted by
//! codepoint for binary search; do not edit by hand.

